{"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"weekNumberingYear"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"get"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function, taken together with "},{"code":"g_date_time_get_week_of_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_date_time_get_day_of_week()"},{"type":"text","text":" can be used to determine the full ISO"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"week date on which ","type":"text"},{"code":"datetime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" falls.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is usually equal to the normal Gregorian year (as returned by","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_date_time_get_year()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), except as detailed below:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Thursday, the week-numbering year is always equal to the usual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year.  For other days, the number is such that every day"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"within a complete week (Monday to Sunday) is contained within the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"same week-numbering year.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"For Monday, Tuesday and Wednesday occurring near the end of the year,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one greater than the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring early in the next year)."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For Friday, Saturday and Sunday occurring near the start of the year,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"this may mean that the week-numbering year is one less than the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"calendar year (so that these days have the same week-numbering year","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as the Thursday occurring late in the previous year)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"An equivalent description is that the week-numbering year is equal to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the calendar year containing the majority of the days in the current"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"week (Monday to Sunday)."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Note that January 1 0001 in the proleptic Gregorian calendar is a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Monday, so this function never returns 0.","type":"text"}]}]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/weekNumberingYear"},"metadata":{"title":"weekNumberingYear","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"property","extendedModule":"GLib","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"weekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib16DateTimeProtocolPAAE17weekNumberingYearSivp::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib11DateTimeRefV","role":"symbol"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/weeknumberingyear"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"kind":"symbol","sections":[],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations":{"title":"DateTimeProtocol Implementations","abstract":[],"kind":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/DateTimeProtocol-Implementations","role":"collectionGroup","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/datetimeprotocol-implementations","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef":{"title":"DateTimeRef","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateTimeRef"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"DateTimeRef"}],"abstract":[{"code":"GDateTime","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is a structure that combines a Gregorian date and time","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into a single structure.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref","type":"topic"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/DateTimeRef/weekNumberingYear":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DateTimeRef\/weekNumberingYear","title":"weekNumberingYear","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/datetimeref\/weeknumberingyear","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"weekNumberingYear","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Returns the ISO 8601 week-numbering year in which the week containing"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"datetime"},{"type":"text","text":" falls."}],"role":"symbol"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib":{"url":"\/documentation\/glib","kind":"symbol","title":"GLib","abstract":[],"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","role":"collection"}}}